# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in any keys you want enabled.
# .env.local is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# All variables MUST be prefixed with VITE_ for Vite to expose them to the
# browser bundle.

# Google Fonts API key — when set, the Edit panel's Font dropdown shows the
# full ~1500-family catalog (sorted by popularity). When unset, the dropdown
# falls back to a curated seed of ~50 popular families.
#
# Get a key:
#   1. Open https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials and create an
#      API key for a project.
#   2. Enable "Web Fonts Developer API" for that project at
#      https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/webfonts.googleapis.com
#   3. (Optional) Restrict the key to your local dev origin
#      (http://localhost:5173/*) under "Application restrictions".
#
# The key is exposed in the dev bundle (Vite inlines VITE_-prefixed vars).
# That's fine for local dev. If you ship a hosted build with the key inlined,
# restrict the key to your production origin first.
VITE_GOOGLE_FONTS_API_KEY=
